        <h2>Welcome to Spencer County</h2>
        <p align="left">Rich in <a title="Felix Stidger : Civil War Hero : Taylorsville resident" href="http://www.wdrb.com/story/29790260/spencer-co-group-working-to-restore-home-of-civil-war-hero" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">history</a> and located in the heart of the Bluegrass, Spencer
         County has the best of the country while only minutes from Louisville, Shelbyville, Bardstown and Lexington,
         Kentucky.</p>
        <p align="left">Boat, swim or fish in the 3,050-acre Taylorsville Lake — the most heavily stocked fishing lake
         in Kentucky! Hike, bike or horseback ride the 24-mile trail system, or enjoy a game of golf with spectacular
         views. The rural atmosphere brings abundant deer and turkey, for nature-lovers and sports enthusiasts.</p>
        <p align="left">Spencer County's friendly Southern hospitality and low crime rate make it a great place to
         come for a relaxing visit and an even better place to call "home." Come and see for yourself, all
         that Spencer County has to offer!</p>
